	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Memphis</placeName> <date>July 16 1862</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>&#33;</p>
				<p>Dear Sir&#33;  At last I can give you again<lb/> some information.  I have been all the time<lb/> well&#44; though suffered much anxiety during<lb/> this war.  You must have heard already that<lb/> I had a law suit with the congregation where<lb/> I am engaged&#44; and that I beat them in the<lb/> first case&#44; and hope to beat them in the second<lb/> for libel&#44; as soon when the courts will be open<lb/> again&#8212;they reckoned behind the host those<lb/> reformers.  I had three counsels employed and<lb/> so had they&#44; the case lasted three and half<lb/> day&#8212;it was hotly contested by them&#44; but they<lb/> knew they had little chance&#44; it was very<lb/> interesting.  In order to get rid of me they accused<lb/> me&#44; that whereas my brother had opened a wholesale<lb/> provision store and <sic>commisary</sic> business and used<lb/> my name is the firm &#40;<persName role="author">Jacob J. Peres</persName> &#38; Co.&#41; and whereas<lb/> he had op<add>&#63;</add> his store on <add>&#63;</add>.  I had<lb/> violated the <date>Shabbath</date>.  My plea was&#44; firstly to<lb/> <sic>shew</sic> &#40;by <add>Hebrew</add> etc&#41; the invalidity of the charge<lb/> and secondly&#44; that malice was the cause of the<lb/> charge&#44; especially my being opposed to reform.  They<lb/> never dreamed that I could give them such good</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>blows&#44; especially that the Lord had given me fully<lb/> a good living&#44; and I could cope with them in any<lb/> way&#44; a poor man had to yield to their machinations.<lb/>  You know I have given <hi rend="underline"><persName>Wise</persName></hi> a thorough thrashing twice<lb/> in the appeal papers&#44; called&#44; him a notorious infidel<lb/> author&#44; have put him on the same level with <persName>Sch&#246;neman<lb/> Patt</persName> from <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName> and <persName>Theodore Parker</persName>.  Do you recollect<lb/> I told you once&#44; to beat them you must give them hard<lb/> blows&#8212;without mercy&#8212;well dear friend I will again<lb/> labor as much I can in our common cause&#44;&#8212;I have<lb/> started at once a new orthodox Congregation&#44; had<lb/> it chartered&#44; we number 55 members&#44; and<lb/> <sic>gess</sic> what name I gave it&#44; just <sic>gess</sic>........<lb/> <hi rend="underline">Beth El Emeth</hi>&#8212;in honor of the minister of the<lb/> Franklin Synagogue in <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>.</p>
				<p>We had a Hazan <persName>Marcuson</persName>&#8212;you know him&#44; he<lb/> is a <add>Hebrew</add>&#44; but is <add>Hebrew</add> and drinks&#8212;hence our<lb/> first trouble&#59; please insert the following<lb/> advertisement.</p>
				<p>Wanted&#44; By the Congregation <hi rend="underline">Beth El Emeth</hi>&#44; <placeName>Memphis<lb/> Tenn.</placeName> Immediately a &#39;Hazan and Sho&#39;het &#38; Bal Horah&#44; None<lb/> but fully competent need to apply.  Salary <del>from &#36;600</del><lb/> <del>to</del> &#36;800.00&#47;100 per annum&#44; besides perquisites.  <sic>testimonials</sic>&#44; and for <sic>farther</sic><lb/> particulars&#44; address to<lb/></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName>L. Alexander</persName>. Prest.<lb/>or <persName role="author">Jacob. J. Peres</persName>. Secy.</p>
				<p>Jewish message copy and bill<lb/> to the Occident.</p>
				<p>Please if possible recommend as a truly competent</p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p>man&#8212;if suitable to the Congr. his salary will be increased.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">You must send me my bill I owe you for some<lb/> <add>Hebrew</add> yet.</p>
				<p>I will send you this or next week the Fifth<lb/> of the articles why do we hide it&#44; I was very<lb/> glad that it was so approved of&#44; I received some<lb/> complementary letters about it from <placeName>New York</placeName>.<lb/> please if possible send me the papers containing<lb/> these articles.</p>
				<p>Hoping to hear from you soon I am</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Respectfully yours</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><persName role="author">Jacob J. Peres</persName></p>
		</body>
